# Inherits the root .clang-tidy. Five checks are relaxed for the Qt desktop
# client only (all stay fully enforced for the rest of src/, which has zero hits
# of any of them). Each is a clash with the Qt/Google house style the module is
# written in, not a latent defect:
#
# - readability-identifier-naming: Qt's API is camelBack (rowCount, headerData,
#   processScan, importSamples), and overriding QAbstractItemModel / QWidget
#   virtuals forces that spelling. The module follows it for its own methods too,
#   for internal consistency. The root rule encodes src's lower_case convention;
#   enforcing it here is a false positive on every Qt override and slot.
# - readability-redundant-access-specifiers: the moc requires a `private slots:`
#   section, which Qt then follows with a plain `private:` for ordinary members.
#   The back-to-back specifiers are mandated by the framework, not redundant.
# - bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters: the service-client wrappers mirror the
#   RPC signatures, which take adjacent string tokens (session_token, lab_id,
#   sample_id, ...). The order is fixed by the proto contract; a caller cannot
#   reasonably transpose them, and wrapping each id in a newtype purely to satisfy
#   the check is churn the proto layer already guards against.
# - modernize-use-nodiscard: every hit is either a Qt virtual override (rowCount,
#   data, columnCount, headerData, canFetchMore — base signatures the module does
#   not own and cannot annotate at the source) or a trivial const UI getter whose
#   result has no side effect to protect. Annotating Qt overrides with
#   [[nodiscard]] is non-idiomatic noise, so the check is disabled here rather
#   than satisfied site-by-site.
# - readability-identifier-length: short, local, throw-away names (loop indices,
#   stream objects) — same rationale as tests/.clang-tidy.
#
# Note: genuine defects the root config caught in this module (a qsizetype->int
# narrowing and a pointer->bool implicit conversion in LoginDialog) were FIXED in
# code, not suppressed — these four relaxations cover only house-style clashes.
InheritParentConfig: true
Checks: >
  -readability-identifier-naming,
  -readability-redundant-access-specifiers,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters,
  -modernize-use-nodiscard,
  -readability-identifier-length
